Southern Capital Group makes 36 cents per share offer for RE&SRead:https://link.theedgesingapore.com/hg4itC8oxQkNE6p36Follow us on:@theedgesg

Judging from the low market participation in this counter and how illiquid it has been  this privatisation offer of $0.36 for RE&S holding does looks very generous and offer a chance for the shareholders to profit off.(Note: this was $0.22 IPO counter)At least  you could safely say that any one who invested in this one and held on didn’t lose. Quite a rare case.Anyways  one more counter off the market . Congrats whoever have this. Just browsed through and it was hovering $0.052 to $0.06x during start of COVID-19. Hence  anyone who bought then and bet on this would have made approx 600 to 650% gain  if still holding on.Seems We would likely see more penny counters get privatised if the lack of market participation carries on. Maybe  the way to trade our market would be to buy those cheap companies and wait it out?Waiting it out does seems an easier option than trying to trade it out in out markets. Just thinking out loud 🤔
